title: Its not Redlining if entire MSA/County is declared as Soft-market" Category 3"
name: Its not Redlining if entire MSA/County is declared as Soft-market" Category 3"
description: One of the largest mortgage lenders in the U.S. recently changed its policy on lending, that almost borders on redlining, in this case they have declared entire counties (across the U.S.) as places where they must have stricter rules for lending money for mortgages. Most of these counties are in California, Florida, Arizona and Nevada. To avoid the litigation, they have declared nearly all counties in some of these MSAs with same category, for eg., category 5 are the ones with the worse performing markets.             They have classified entire MSAs/Counties into risk categories between 1 and 5, where 5 is the highest risk market.                         Source: http://www.socketsite.com/archives/2008/01/san_francisco_currently_a_category_two_soft_market_to_c_1.html            and the links mentioned in the blog            See whats redlining: http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Redlining
